resources.description:
This route register a new user.
### Required Body Content
* Name
* E-mail
* CPF
* Adress
  * CEP
  * Logradouro
  * Complemento
  * Bairro
  * Localidade
  * UF
* Password
* Image ( base64 )


#### Admin Users
For register an admin user is necessary to pass another topic on the Body content: access_level.
* 1 <= access_level <= 3

For market employees the access_level is equal to 2

For admin users the access_level is equal to 3


### Return
Returns an object with the:
* User registered +
  * *active attribute as false by default*
* *Json Web Token as well*.
resources.name: Register User

resources.description:
This route authenticates an user.


### Required Body Content
* E-mail
* Password


### Return
Returns an object with the:
* User authenticated
* *Json Web Token*.
resources.name: Authenticate

resources.description:
This route lists all users registered.


### Required Headers
* Authorization: *Json Web Token*

### Optional Query Params
* active=true: returns all users that have made at least one purchase


### Return
* An array with all users registered
resources.name: List All

resources.description:
This route list the one user requested


### Required Headers Content
* Authorization: *Json Web Token*

### Required Route Params
* Id of the client


### Return
Returns the requested user.

* tag=<name_of_tag>: returns all products with that tag

  * for decrescent pattern use the '-' caracter before the sort name
